comments.body:
[~kmeredith]: 
1. Yes, confirmed. Also, a bucket can be referenced equivalently two ways, not sure why, probably for compatibility with AWS, but we might as well tell people about it:

{noformat}
mybucket.objectstorage.mycloud.example.com
mybucket.s3.mycloud.example.com
{noformat}

2. Assuming walrusbackend.storagemaxbucketsizeinmb is still a property, then confirmed.

However, [~sjones], why are the only properties in euctl for walrus these 4? (same as what you listed above)

{noformat}
walrusbackend.blockdevice =
walrusbackend.resource =
walrusbackend.storagedir = ///var/lib/eucalyptus/bukkits
walrusbackend.storagemaxtotalcapacity = 0
{noformat}

If I try to set any of these other properties, I can't:

{noformat}
# euctl walrusbackend.storagemaxbucketsizeinmb=100
euctl: error (ModifyPropertyValueType): Failed to set property: No such property: walrusbackend.storagemaxbucketsizeinmb
{noformat}

Is that because they're no longer used? I still see references to them in the code, in this case in {{Walrusinfo.java}}:

{noformat}
  @Column(name = "storage_max_bucket_size_mb")
  private Integer storageMaxBucketSizeInMB;
{noformat}

...and in the DB:

{noformat}
eucalyptus_shared=# select * from walrus_info;
                id                |   creation_timestamp    |  last_update_timestamp  |          metadata_perm_uuid          | versi
on | storage_walrus_bucket_names_require_compliance | walrus_name |         storage_dir          | storage_max_bucket_size_mb | stor
age_max_buckets_per_user | storage_walrus_total_capacity | storage_snapshot_size_gb
----------------------------------+-------------------------+-------------------------+--------------------------------------+------
---+------------------------------------------------+-------------+------------------------------+----------------------------+-----
-------------------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------
 8aef81c8552db69301552db70b5b0177 | 2016-06-07 18:53:38.651 | 2016-06-07 18:53:38.651 | 7ea6a187-aaff-4a6a-bcdc-fd2243aa29bb |
 0 | f                                              | Walrus      | //var/lib/eucalyptus/bukkits |                       5120 |
                     100 |                             0 |                       50
(1 row)
{noformat}

3. Confirmed, if those are indeed still properties. As for storagemaxcachesizeinmb, I see no references in the 4.2.2 or 4.3 code, and nothing that looks like any replacement, so I think you can remove all references to this in the docs.

4. Confirmed, but why did you change the case? Typo? storagedir is correct, not storageDir.

5. Confirmed for 4.2.2 For 4.3, euca_conf will respond like:

{noformat}
# euca_conf --register-walrusbackend
error: euca_conf is no longer supported.  Use ``euserv-register-service -t walrusbackend'' and ``clcadmin-copy-keys'' for this operation instead.
{noformat}

6-8: I'll provide feedback soon.
